						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1435 (1513 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Fragmentary. Seems to refer to a gift of land as <hi rend="italic">tiruviḍaiyāṭṭam.</hi> The details of the date viz. <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1435, Śrīmukha, Makara, śu. 1 ••••• Śravaṇa, Makara-saṅkrānti</hi> regularly correspond to <hi rend="bold">1513 A.D., December 28, the week day was Wednesday, ·27, f.d.n. ·19.</hi></p>						

